  "body": "- [ ] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nAfter upgrading truffle to version 5.4.3, the compilation fails on all Import statements (refer to example below). \r\n\r\nERROR (for one import, but receiving the same error for all imports):\r\nParserError: Source \"node_modules/@openzeppelin/contracts-upgradeable/proxy/utils/Initializable.sol\" not found\r\n --> project:/contracts/CryptoAstres.sol:4:1:\r\n  |\r\n import \"../../node_modules/@openzeppelin/contracts-upgradeable/proxy/utils/Initializable.sol\";\r\n  | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\r\n\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nUpgrade and compile contract.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nSuccessful compilation. \r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nPlease see above.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Ubuntu 20.04, up to date\r\n* Ethereum client: Ganache\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.4.3\r\n* node version (`node --version`): 14.17.4\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): 7.20.3\r\n\r\n",
